Ed,<br><br>
I chose to believe.  Like it too much not to.  BY the way I remember that SOS attempt.  Spelling still bad.  You left out the &quot;p&quot;.  I saw the message SAM SAM SAM.  Scared the shit out me and I hauled ass.  Sorry about that.<br><br>
Never got too personal with the weapon I carried.  For a fly boy a weapon was considered something you shot at the enemy to ensure they killed you quickly.  Just checked out what ever the armory had when the days missions started.  Shit it would be too hard to run away with an M60.  That's the reason they issued them, too heavy to run.  Had to stay and fight.  You know a Marine would never leave his weapon.  Smart, do you think they ever figured it out.<br><br>
Two things I was always with and very particular about.  First I kept my can opener on my dog chains.  Always preflighted the little sucker, never without it.  I never knew they kept it a secret from the Jarheads until now  Understand the power it possessed.  Used it to slay the powerful ration beast.  I always believed it could cut through anything.  You sure that story isn't true?  At least the hippie part?<br><br>
Second were my knives.  Serious about them.  Kept two always razor sharp.  One standard issue and one seal model.  Still have both and still maintain razor sharp.  Just checked on them before this post.<br><br>
Depressed now.  I have lost the trusty can opener.<br><br>

